  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated  Sustainable Livelihood forMountain Dalits - 2nd Phase</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project already completed 3 years and in the first phase live stocks of goats and poultries have been distributed and beneficiaries have been capacity building in the livelstock livelihoods and have been given training on best practices being followed in this field.  Goats kids were recycled and eggs were sold by women so that the women engaged are able to earn some income. 2.In the proposed 4th year project will focus on strengthening on developing a collective institution (Federation) which will carry forward the work after project withdrawal. Programme will also initiate a Goat resource centre (GRC) which will breed and supply goats to new partners and groups</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To establish an institution as a successful business enterprise it is necessary to upscale it to a level where the enterprise could produce at scale and plan for collective marketing of the produce.  The project will 25 villages in 2 blocks and 2 districts of himachal Pradesh.  The community will be able to generate income and also malnutrition issues of women and girls will also be improved through kitchen garden initiative.</narrative>
  </description>
